  "title": "Operation Executive (Logistic)",
  "description": "<p>Job responsibilities : </p><ul><li>Manage stakeholders and teams to ensure completion of tasks and activities</li></ul><ul><li>Oversee warehouse operations, including layout, storage, material handling, and relocations</li></ul><ul><li>Implement process improvements and optimize use of resources</li></ul><ul><li>Monitor and manage transportation and cargo operations efficiently</li></ul><ul><li>Ensure safety, health, and WSH compliance, conducting risk assessments and corrective actions</li></ul><ul><li>Manage key accounts, maintain stakeholder relationships, and support service delivery</li></ul><ul><li>Develop warehouse security plans and manage handling of hazardous or sensitive materials</li></ul><ul><li>Apply quality management principles to enhance operational standards</li></ul><ul><li>Identify areas where technology can improve logistics processes</li></ul><ul><li><p>Execute risk mitigation plans and address operational issues<br /></p><p><br />Job requirement</p></li><li><p>Basic knowledge of SAP/Warehouse Management System (WMS)/Supply Chain Software/Enterprise Resource Planning (ERP) Systems<br />Proficiency in basic Microsoft (MS) Office/Power Platform Applications</p></li><li>Degree/Diploma in Business/Logistics/Supply Chain or equivalent certifications</li><li>1-3 years of relevant working experience in Warehouse Operations/Vendor Management</li></ul>",
